 geometry (or platelet geometry), we consider cubes. The results can be\napplied to design both purely solid-state opto-electronic devices and systems\nfor photo-catalysis and solar conversion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 May 2013 19:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 8 Jun 2013 12:06:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 19 Sep 2013 18:51:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-20"}
